{"sections":[{"estimatedTimeInMinutes":45,"image":"ic_theme_intro.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s suppose we want to define a view for corporate apps with headings, texts, buttons and images.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"How can we do that?","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"hero","title":"Define information cards","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.4","projectFiles":"OUDS-Onboarding-Tutorial.zip","backgroundImage":"ic_theme_intro.png","chapter":"Define information cards"},{"tasks":[{"anchor":"Define-the-view-basics","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before designing awesome SwiftUI view with OUDS, we need to write before the properties of such view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You should have an access to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.figma.com\/design\/zJl6GhY2gMSMAibBJXoNPy\/Reveal-and-Onboarding?node-id=2259-4970&m=dev","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":"Define the view basics","stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-1.png","type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Define a basic "},{"code":"InfoCard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it must have an asset name to load as image, a title, a subtitle, a description and a label for the button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Add also the Xcode "},{"code":"#Preview","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" macro to display the view, here of course it will be empty."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-1.swift"},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Supposing we will work with Orange theme here, apply the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"orangePreview()"},{"text":" view modifier.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS library provides view modifiers to be used in Xcode previews macros.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It allows to apply the theme you want in the view","type":"text"}]}],"code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-2.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-1.png","media":null},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now, use the properties you defined in the Xcode preview, and display them in your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InfoCard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" containing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Image"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" objects."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-3.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-3.png"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You may want to apply typography on texts. These effects will show most important content and bring meanings."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can have a look on the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/swiftuicore\/view","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which can be applied on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"title","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" with want a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"medium heading","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", an "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"XL heading","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"subtitle","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"large default body","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"description","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":". You will need to get the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" object throw the dedicated environment variable to give it to the view modifiers."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-4.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-4.png"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, it’s time to apply colors on texts. "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/colorsemantictokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. small atomic elements defined in the design Figma kit. The "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" object contains tokens and provides them thanks to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"providers","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For all texts, change the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"foreground color","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":": apply "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"contentBrandPrimary","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"title","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"contentDefault","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the subtitle and also the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"description","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-5.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-5.png"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, it’s time to add the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". OUDS provides plenty of components with properties related to notions defined in Figma kit and DSM. For example a button can have "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"appearance","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a button with a "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton#Appearances","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", using the previously defined label, and no action."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-6.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-6.png"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You agree things are stucked and spacings are missing. "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/spacesemantictokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some of these tokens have unique value like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme.spaces.fixedMedium"},{"type":"text","text":", but "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/spacemultiplesemantictokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" depending to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"size class","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of the view like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme.spaces.scaled2xsmall"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, OUDS provides view modifiers to define "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"grid margins","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" on a view depending to a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"size class","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Try to apply some spacings: "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"fixedNone","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"fixedMedium","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Spacer"},{"type":"text","text":" minimum length below the button, "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"top grid margin","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"title","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"grid margin","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for all the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"scaled2xsmall","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" as "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"vertical padding","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"subtitle","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"scaledLarge","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" as minimum length for a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Spacer"},{"type":"text","text":" above the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"button","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","code":"tutorial-onboarding-2-7.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-onboarding-2-7.png"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to force the "},{"i